    public class WekaMatchingRule<RecordType extends Matchable,SchemaElementType extends Matchable>
extends FilteringMatchingRule<RecordType,SchemaElementType>
implements LearnableMatchingRule<RecordType,SchemaElementType>
    Class that creates and applies a matching Rule based on supervised learning using the Weka Library.

    • Constructor Detail

      • WekaMatchingRule

        public WekaMatchingRule(double finalThreshold,
                        String classifierName,
                        String[] parameters)
        Create a MatchingRule, which can be trained using the Weka library for identity resolution.
        Parameters:
        finalThreshold - determines the confidence level, which needs to be exceeded by the classifier, so that it can classify a record as match.
        classifierName - Has the name of a specific classifier from the Weka library.
        parameters - Hold the parameters to tune the classifier.

      • WekaMatchingRule

        public WekaMatchingRule(double finalThreshold)
        Create an empty MatchingRule without any classifier. The classifier has to be added later on, which can be trained using the Weka library for identity resolution.
        Parameters:
        finalThreshold - determines the confidence level, which needs to be exceeded by the classifier, so that it can classify a record as match.

      • apply

        public Correspondence<RecordType,SchemaElementType> apply(RecordType record1,
                                                          RecordType record2,
                                                          Processable<Correspondence<SchemaElementType,Matchable>> schemaCorrespondences)
        Apply trained model to a candidate record-pair. Therefore a new FeatureDataSet is created, which is afterwards classified as match or non-match
        Specified by:
        apply in class FilteringMatchingRule<RecordType extends Matchable,SchemaElementType extends Matchable>
        Parameters:
        record1 - the first record (must not be null)
        record2 - the second record (must not be null)
        schemaCorrespondences - the schema correspondences between the first and the second records
        Returns:
        A correspondence holding the input parameters plus the classification´s result, which is either match (1.0) or non-match(0.0).
